<font color="#FF0000">QUESTIONS FOR DOC SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Sun Mar  9 22:16:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc Spatz:<br><br>
&gt;&quot;If anything that is common to vietnam vets, it is that THEY DON'T KNOW HOW TO LAUGH about things they should.&quot;&lt;<br><br>
OK, tell me *specifically* in your opinion what we should laugh about and how to go about laughing about it. Try a list, you know, 1.., 2.., 3.. etc.<br><br>
&gt;&quot;I know the bush was bad, but 30 years later you got to have a sense of humor, or my associates and their butterfly nets will snag you.&quot;&lt; <br><br>
OK, you are right. The bush was bad. But how does humor enter into it. I have a lot of dealings with your &quot;associates and their butterfly nets&quot;. In fact, they sometimes &quot;snag&quot; me weekly. None of them has ever, ever, ever suggested humor as a therapy. In fact, none of them has ever, ever, ever laughed at what I have said. I guess I haver no capacity for humor in this. Poor me! The butterfly nets must be missing the point, too. Please be specific and discuss the humor you feel compelled to recommend. Black humor, white humor, slapstick.. you know!<br><br>
&gt;&quot;Understand? I don't mean to insult, or to laugh about fire fights and trip wires, only to tell you that LIFE GOES ON, and you have to deal with it. PERIOD.&quot;&lt;<br><br>
An interesting philosophy. Stuff it all back down inside, put your chin up, stand at attention, and march off the edge of the cliff you are desparately trying to avoid in the first place by permitting yourself to get snagged by the boys with the butterfly nets. How do you recommend we &quot;deal with it&quot;. Many of us have tried alcohol, drugs, suicide, violence, anger, and all that good stuff that can come out in &quot;dealing&quot; with things isolated from professional help and the support of our buddies. Of course life goes on, but you think we are not a part of it? Be specific. And what do you mean by &quot;period&quot;. Are you attemping to convey a sense of authority in this? Are you attempting to motivate us to go along with your ideas? Do you think it is for our own good?<br>
I really need more information to form an opinion of your words.<br><br>
Thanks for your concern.<br><br>
Arthur<br>
   
